        },
        {
          "username": "Michael Siu (DJ OLB)",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "115536679154066167388",
          "user_review_count": 39,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX20qYMVAznXMQ4YW5Ff6QrTkrSpHtB-6pkbo_loBJFvQJdN_AQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Such unprofessionalism. Doctor assigned does not disclose closing the account and testing kit was sent yet voided making two weeks of waiting go by without knowing or treatment. If testing is free and you don't know if you are at risk what's the point of advertising the free test and sending it out. Either fix your system or hire some better professionals, absolute joke of a company and standards.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2t0YWNYQnhURkpSWDJNd1UyNVNjbU0yU0ZCTlNWRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc55e5184274e5f25!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOktacXBxTFJRX2MwU25ScmM2SFBNSVE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-02-15T21:26:12+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Dylan Marone",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "109819128141920905788",
          "user_review_count": 41,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcJeB0rPTAjIaBsjX0tk_5EEnqxig3tmRZ91vpGWVFp2VHm416=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "The last 2 years using Mistr and it just keeps getting more and more complicated and extremely disorganized. Waiting 3-4 days for a message to be answered, as that's their only way of communication, is crazy. Then you have to call and be the middle man between them and the pharmacy and the pharmacy never seems to get the correct info. What should be such a great program/service is an absolute nightmare of a company.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkeGIwVTRiMTlwTUZKQ2JqUldOR3cxT1Rsck5tYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc55e5184274e5f25!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjdxb0U4b19pMFJCbjRWNGw1OTlrNmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-03-26T23:00:55+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "SONNY LAW",
          "rating": 2,
          "contributor_id": "117150586909740821080",
          "user_review_count": 38,
          "user_photo_count": 13,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgY-TGaucSE4rsAcEy2OR804AowemoYquTDAwmPaCp0tDHN_HU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This is my review and these are my opinions. I attempted to sign up with MISTR about two years ago and that was unsuccessful. At that time, I was having extreme difficulty with staff/agent(s) lack of professionalism, never receiving timely and concise responses to very personal in nature questions/inquiries. I felt a disconnection with MISTR's Mission and Objectives....IMO- global education and awareness, eliminate the spread of HIV and some STI's, and the bottom line being; saving lives. I sent a lengthy and affectionate \"Dear John\" and stated my qualms, my interactions and overall experience, and my reasons for not moving forward with MISTR.\nFAST FORWARD\nIn the back of my mind, I was second guessing whether my standards were too high and did my personal ethics and views prevent my own life from being saved with a free prescription from MISTR for PREP and PEP Doxy. So, I contacted MISTR once again to restart the application process. I, once again, ran into the same issues with professionalism, communication, and respect but this time I was well equipped and proactive in foreseeing obstacles, and kept communication to a bare minimum. After almost a year, I received my first prescription delivery,  provided and paid for by MISTR and affiliates. Thank you! And ever since, I continue to receive on a monthly basis. Does require you to respond to text messages about approving shipment of meds, verifying shipping address, and signing by signature that you received your prescription(s).\nSumming it up! I do what needs to be done to get the free meds. If I had to pay out of pocket for MISTR's prescription program, would I? Hell no! I am too \"old school\" and customer service oriented. To be honest and keeping it real, real. I sold out for the freebies, but these freebies saves lives and will prevent me from infection of the HIV virus!!!!! That's a win in my book\ud83d\ude1c",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT200MlR6bENiMEpzVEhsa2IycGZabFk0WTBkaVVrRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc55e5184274e5f25!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm42TzlCb0JsTHlkb2pfZlY4Y0diUkE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 5 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-01-05T05:44:11+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Daniel Chavez",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "115115829079592448901",
          "user_review_count": 35,
          "user_photo_count": 16,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3gEU4j_V3IHQdyYJ1KtXuyOiDJRFb8juR_y-2Zocc28i6oG6h=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Beyond easy. The test kits are just as easy to do and the finger poke is almost pain-free. Support is always available and the folks that work their make it so smooth to get your meds. Love love love MISTR. They make me feel welcomed and I know I'm safe with them.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21oQ1QwNHRZemRLU0ZSYVZUWnlUWFJLTTJwTVkzYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xc55e5184274e5f25!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmhCT04tYzdKSFRaVTZyTXRKM2pMY3c%7C%7C?hl=en",
